  "system": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<p>At 17th level, your control over the elements is now almost second nature, allowing you to do things almost subconsciously. When a creature makes a saving throw against a jutsu corresponding with your nature release granted by your <em><strong>Natural Proficiency</strong></em> they subtract 1d4 from their result.</p><p>Additionally, once per turn when you damage a creature suffering from the condition corresponding to your <em><strong>Natural End Table</strong></em> choice, you may trigger <em><strong>Lethal Attack</strong></em> on any creature(s) damaged, as long as they are also suffering from that condition.</p><p>Finally, when you deal damage to a creature corresponding <em><strong>Natural End Table</strong></em> damage type they must make a Constitution saving throw against your Ninjutsu Save DC or gain 1 rank of the listed condition.</p>",
